text.section:
Before the Commissioner issues a certificate of qualification to an applicant, the applicant shall file with the Commissioner a bond that:
is subject to approval by the Commissioner;
runs to the State;
is executed by the applicant as principal and by a corporate surety insurer authorized to do business in the State;
is in the penal sum of $10,000; and
is conditioned that the broker will:
conduct business in accordance with this article; and
remit promptly the taxes required by § 3-324 of this subtitle.
